            "en": "<p></p><p>You are eligible for a collective debt settlement if you are struggling with large <strong>structural debts<strong> that you cannot possibly repay within a reasonable time. A collective debt settlement is therefore not intended to settle temporary payment problems.<p><p><strong>Traders<strong>, just like forms of companies (nv, bvba,...) are not eligible. In the event of structural debt problems, they can invoke a <strong>bankruptcy<strong>. In the event of temporary defaults, they can invoke the law '<strong>Continuity of enterprises<strong>'.<p><p><a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"58502ec9-123e-4b52 -9cca-4d590ae2ce4e\" data-content-type=\"Website\" href=\"http://www.eerstehulpbijschulden.be/schulden-wat-nu/hulp-nodig/collectieve-schuldenregeling/aanvraag-en-toelating\" target=\"_blank\" rel =\"noopener\" class=\"vl-link vl-link--inline\">A more comprehensive overview of the conditions<span class=\"vl-link__icon vl-link__icon--after vl-vi vl-vi- external\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span><span class=\"vl-u-visually-hidden\"> ((opens in new window))<span><a> can be found on the First aid for debts website.<p></p>",
