            "en": "<p></p><h3>Petition</h3><p>You apply for a collective debt settlement with a petition in duplicate to the <a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"7653832e-0634-40bf-a3a4-8a0549416ded\" data-content-type=\"Website\" href=\"https://territoriale-bevoegdheid.just.fgov.be\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"vl-link vl-link--inline\">labor court<span class=\"vl-link__icon vl-link__icon--after vl-vi vl-vi-external\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><span class=\"vl-u-visually-hidden\"> ((opent in nieuw venster))</span></a>of the district where you live.</p><p>To prepare this petition, visit a <a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"5209c3c7-bb3b-4672-9be7-8810e23f785a\" data-content-type=\"Article\" href=\"/gemeenten-en-provincies/organisatie-en-werking-van-gemeenten/contactgegevens-van-lokale-besturen\">OCMW</a>in your municipality or a<a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"f9f21cad-031f-41f8-a82c-7e5207e61024\" data-content-type=\"Topic\" href=\"/caw-centrum-voor-algemeen-welzijnswerk\">CAW</a> in your region. You can also draft the application yourself. Inform yourself about this at the labor court of your place of residence.</p><h3>Mediation</h3><p>If you are admitted to a collective debt settlement, the judge will determine a recognized<strong>debt mediator</strong> at. The debt mediator is independent and will therefore take equal account with your interests as with the interests of your creditors.</p><ul><li>Through mediation, the debt mediator will try to reach an agreement between you and your creditors<a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"128fb086-e1ca-43bd-be78-b972e250673d\" data-content-type=\"Website\" href=\"http://www.eerstehulpbijschulden.be/schulden-wat-nu/hulp-nodig/collectieve-schuldenregeling/minnelijke-aanzuiveringsregeling\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"vl-link vl-link--inline\">amicable settlement arrangement<span class=\"vl-link__icon vl-link__icon--after vl-vi vl-vi-external\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><span class=\"vl-u-visually-hidden\">((opens in new window))</span></a>to come.</li><li>If this does not work, he will draw up a report and the judge can make a decision based on that<a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"6d400bbd-82e2-410f-b674-640ac4e96406\" data-content-type=\"Website\" href=\"http://www.eerstehulpbijschulden.be/schulden-wat-nu/hulp-nodig/collectieve-schuldenregeling/gerechtelijke-aanzuiveringsregeling\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"vl-link vl-link--inline\">judicial settlement arrangement<span class=\"vl-link__icon vl-link__icon--after vl-vi vl-vi-external\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><span class=\"vl-u-visually-hidden\"> ((opens in new window))</span></a>impose.</li><li>In exceptional cases, a<a data-language=\"nl\" data-identifier=\"dd9f72de-7403-4fdc-a09b-8eaf29f87b51\" data-content-type=\"Website\" href=\"http://www.eerstehulpbijschulden.be/schulden-wat-nu/hulp-nodig/collectieve-schuldenregeling/totale-kwijtschelding\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"vl-link vl-link--inline\">total debt forgiveness<span class=\"vl-link__icon vl-link__icon--after vl-vi vl-vi-external\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><span class=\"vl-u-visually-hidden\">((opens in new window))</span></a>be asked to the judge.</li></ul></p>",
